name: Create webRTC
keepData
func:
const config = flow.get("myenv")
const ip = config.internalIPv4
const publicStream = config.publicStream
const hwId = msg.data.hwId
const result = msg.payload.status
const storeId = msg.storeId
var streamPort = null
if (result == 1) {
    msg.collection = "status"
    msg.operation = "updateOne"
    switch (msg.data.stationType) {
        case 'Pig Classification':
            streamPort = "rtsp://" + ip + ":" + config.aiStreamPortClassification + "/ds-test"
            break
        case 'Belly Grading':
            streamPort = "rtsp://" + ip + ":" + config.aiStreamPortBelly + "/ds-test"
            break
        default:
            streamPort = "rtsp://" + ip + ":" + config.aiStreamPortClassification + "/ds-test"
    } 
    const data = {
        "message": "AI service is running",
        "notify": "AI " + msg.data.stationType + " job is started",
        "stationType": msg.data.stationType,
        "aiId": msg.aiId,
        "cameraUrl": msg.data.cameraUrl,
        "streamUrl": streamPort,
        "webRTC": "http://" + ip + ":8083/stream/" + hwId + "/channel/0/webrtc",
        "eventAddress": ip,
        "eventPort": 8081,
        "publicStream": publicStream
    }
    msg.result = data
    msg.payload = [{ _id: storeId }, { $set: data }]
    return [msg, null]
} else {
    msg.payload = {
        "message": "Error something wrong"
    }
    return [null, msg]
}

const replyToken = msg.payload.events[0].replyToken
const message = msg.payload.events[0]
if (replyToken) {
  const orderId = msg.payload.events[0].message.text.match(/orderId: (\w+)/)[1]
  msg.collection = "request"
  msg.operation = "aggregate"

  var joinField = [
    { "$match": { "orderId": orderId } },
  ]
  msg.replyToken = replyToken
  msg.message = message
  msg.payload = [joinField]
  return msg
}

name: replyToken
func:
const status = msg.payload
if (status) {
    const replyToken = msg.replyToken
    const replyId = msg.payload[0]._id
    const userId = msg.message.source.userId
    msg.collection = "request"
    msg.operation = "updateOne"
    const requestData = Object.assign({
        "userId": userId,
        "replyToken": replyToken
        
    })
    msg.payload = [{ _id: replyId }, { $set: requestData }]
    return msg
}
